###to clone code use:

1) create a folder 
2) open folder in vs code 
3) run git clone {repository URL} on terminal

###if u have to puch code on existing repo:

if you face any issue while deploying on github go in the folders--> views --> click on hidden folders and delete .git file
1) git init
2) git add .
3) git status
4) git commit -m "commit name"
5) git remote add origin <<repo url>>
   if this error comes fatal: remote origin already exists.
      use--> git remote rm origin
      then use 5 command again
6) git push origin master    or     git push origin master --force

###if u have to puch code on new repo:

1) git init
2) git origin.... whole this give on new repo page(better write it to avoid error)
3) git add .
4) git status
5) git commit -m "commit name"
6) git push origin master

###how to push code on heroku

1) heroku login
2) heroku create <<domain name>>
3) git push heroku master
